				<div class="box">
			<h3>Editorial comment</h3>
			<p> It should be noted that Costa Rica’s exports to the EU under the tariff-only regime increased at twice the rate of ACP banana exports. This may in part account for Costa Rica’s reluctance to join Ecuador in challenging the EU banana regime. There have been diverse trends in banana supplies to the EU market since the introduction of the tariff-only regime. These trends can only partly be attributed to the implementation of the new regime. Other important factors include:</p>
<ul>

<li> a bounce back from weather-related fluctuations;</li>

<li> comprehensive investments in industry development and technological improvements in some countries;</li>

<li> the strengthening of the ‘fair trade’ market;</li>

<li> difficulties in securing transportation in the face of shortages of reefer capacity in the light of China’s thirst for commodities.</li>

</ul>

		</div>
		
